06:19.440 --> 06:21.440
It's completely unsustainable.

06:21.440 --> 06:23.440
We are exploiting our planet.

06:23.440 --> 06:29.440
We're exploiting ourselves in order to sustain the economic model that reigns.

06:29.440 --> 06:35.440
And then there's the kind of the model of social, of relationship,

06:35.440 --> 06:40.440
not just social relations between humans, but relationship with ourselves individually,

06:40.440 --> 06:46.440
with each other, and then with the more than human natural world.

06:46.440 --> 06:52.440
And in both of these, like both relationship and the economic model,

06:52.440 --> 07:01.440
I feel as though without reimagining masculinity, which has shaped our largest economies

07:01.440 --> 07:07.440
and family structures that feed into economies and so on.

07:07.440 --> 07:13.440
And also, I guess, a kind of quest to explore other parts of the world,

07:13.440 --> 07:17.440
which has resulted in colonialism and neocolonialism.

07:17.440 --> 07:25.440
It's men who have done these things and continue to largely lead the world.

07:25.440 --> 07:34.440
