09:35.440 --> 09:40.440
even though it's about masculinity and not maleness or being a man.

09:40.440 --> 09:44.440
Nonetheless, the first reaction was one of really, can this be true?

09:44.440 --> 09:47.440
There's such great men out there. Can it really be inherently about masculinity?

09:47.440 --> 09:49.440
For me, it's more to do with design.

09:49.440 --> 09:55.440
It's how we've designed a public space and that men have designed a public space in a certain way.

09:55.440 --> 10:02.440
And it's not holistic. It doesn't really draw on the more complex resources that we have.

10:02.440 --> 10:10.440
If there's a problem, it's the lack of culturally appropriate, sacred initiation into the masculine.

10:10.440 --> 10:16.440
And that's what we lost. And ever since we lost it, patriarchy developed.

10:16.440 --> 10:21.440
