14:14.440 --> 14:24.440
But one of the clarifications to make again is that, of course, to Dominique's point, masculinity is intersectional, you could say.

14:24.440 --> 14:33.440
So it's layered with race and ethnicity and culture and class and all of those kinds of things.

14:33.440 --> 14:39.440
The reason that the question I think is far more important than the question of just human interactions

14:39.440 --> 14:47.440
is because we are talking about things like toxic masculinity and crisis and masculinity.

14:47.440 --> 14:53.440
And even the conversation here in this room has kind of been talking a lot about kind of striving for balance

14:53.440 --> 14:57.440
and we brought up male pain, if you like.

14:57.440 --> 15:00.440
And I do want to acknowledge that that exists and it's important to talk about.

15:00.440 --> 15:05.440
